leads.lead_text: Leaves pinnate, leaflets 5–7, rarely trifoliolate near base of plant; East Gippsland only
Keel glabrous or not conspicuously ciliate along margins
Shrubs to 3 m tall; leaflets 2–6 mm wide, margins flat or recurved; calyx more than 10 mm long; corolla 20–30 mm long
Shrubs usually less than 1 m tall; leaflets 0.5–2 mm wide, margins revolute; calyx usually less than 10 mm long; corolla 15–20 mm long
Stems tuberculate; corolla pale lemon-yellow or yellow-green; East Gippsland only
Stems not tuberculate; corolla apricot, red or purplish (rarely yellow in G. ecostatum)
Stipules absent; stems glabrous or minutely hairy with curled hairs; corolla red to purple; probably not in Victoria, see note below genus description
Stipules subulate; stems covered with short, spreading hairs; corolla apricot to reddish, rarely yellow
